          "media": {
            "id": "fs-id1462948",
            "alt": "The left part of this image shows a plant cell bathed in a hypertonic solution so that the plasma membrane has pulled away completely from the cell wall, and the central vacuole has shrunk. Water moves out of the plant cell. The middle part shows a plant cell bathed in an isotonic solution; the plasma membrane has pulled away from the cell wall a bit, and the central vacuole size is unchanged. Water moves both in and out of the plant cell. The right part shows a plant cell in a hypotonic solution. The central vacuole is large, and the plasma membrane is pressed against the cell wall. Water is moving into the plant cell.",
            "src": "../../media/Figure_05_02_08-2288.jpg",
            "mimeType": "image/jpg"
          }
        },
